Masood Textile Mills (MTM) is a vertically-integrated textile manufacturing company based out of Faisalabad, Pakistan with in-house yarn, knitting, fabric dyeing, processing, laundry and apparel manufacturing facilities. MTM is publicly listed on the Pakistan Stock Exchange. It is currently the largest knit-wear manufacturer and exporter in Pakistan.
In 2014 it posted a pre-tax profit of Rs 1.1 billion, which was 13% higher than its pre-tax earnings in the preceding year. Shanghai Challenge Textile Company acquired 24.3% shares in Masood Textile Mills in a privately negotiated deal.
